withMinEvictableIdleTime

public KijiTableReaderPool.Builder withMinEvictableIdleTime(long minEvictableIdleTime)
Set the time in milliseconds after which a reader may be evicted for idleness. Readers are not guaranteed to be evicted when this time has elapsed, but they may not be evicted before it. This field is optional and defaults to GenericObjectPool.DEFAULT_MIN_EVICTABLE_IDLE_TIME_MILLIS.

Parameters:
minEvictableIdleTime - time in milliseconds a reader must remain idle before it may be evicted.
Returns:
this.

withTimeBetweenEvictionRuns

public KijiTableReaderPool.Builder withTimeBetweenEvictionRuns(long timeBetweenEvictionRuns)
Set the time in milliseconds between automatic eviction of idle readers. This field is optional and defaults to GenericObjectPool.DEFAULT_TIME_BETWEEN_EVICTION_RUNS_MILLIS.

Parameters:
timeBetweenEvictionRuns - time in milliseconds to wait between evicting readers which have been idle longer than the allowed duration.

withColumnReaderSpecAlternatives

public KijiTableReaderPool.Builder withColumnReaderSpecAlternatives(com.google.common.collect.Multimap<KijiColumnName,ColumnReaderSpec> alternatives)
Set the ColumnReaderSpec alternatives for which cell decoders will be available, but which will not change the default behavior of read requests. Column name, ColumnReaderSpec pairs in this list will not trigger failures when OnDecoderCacheMiss is set to FAIL. This field may not be set with CellSpec overrides.

Parameters:
alternatives - mapping from column names to alternative ColumnReaderSpecs which will be available from readers served by this pool.
Returns:
this.
